cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with multi-person pose estimation. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new network architecture for pose estimation. Additionally, it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with image and video data. Finally, it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a new neural network architecture.
